===Noun===
{{en-noun|spectr|a}}

# A [[range]]; a [[continuous]], [[infinite]], [[one-dimensional]] set, possibly bounded by [[extremes]].
# ''Specifically,'' a range of [[colour]]s representing [[light]] ([[electromagnetic radiation]]) of contiguous [[frequency|frequencies]]; hence ''[[electromagnetic spectrum]]'', ''[[visible spectrum]]'', ''[[ultraviolet spectrum]]'', etc.
# {{chemistry}} The pattern of [[absorption]] or [[emission]] of [[radiation]] produced by a substance when subjected to energy (radiation, heat, electricity, etc.).
# {{linearalg}} of a [[bounded linear operator]] ''A'', the [[scalar]] values λ such that the [[operator]] ''A—λI'', where ''I'' denotes the identity operator, does not have a bounded [[inverse]]

